@startuml Execute Saved Report Flow
title Demo App Flow: Execute Saved Report Directly

actor "End-User" as User
participant "Demo App UI" as UI
participant "ReportBuilderController" as Controller
participant "ReportBuilderRequest\n(Factory)" as Factory
participant "DynamicReport Engine" as Engine
database "Database" as DB

User -> UI : Open "Saved Reports Library"
activate UI
User -> UI : Click "Execute Live"
UI -> Controller : GET /saved/{id}/execute
activate Controller

Controller -> DB : Find SavedReport by ID
activate DB
DB --> Controller : SavedReport Instance (with Payload)
deactivate DB

Controller -> Factory : ReportBuilderRequest::createFromSavedReport(SavedReport)
activate Factory
Factory --> Controller : ReportBuilderRequest DTO
deactivate Factory
note right: Completely bypasses UI serialization.\nExecutes strictly from DB state.

Controller -> Engine : DynamicReport::generate(ReportRequest)
activate Engine
Engine -> DB : Execute Optimized Query
activate DB
DB --> Engine : Result Set
deactivate DB
Engine --> Controller : Paginated Data
deactivate Engine

Controller --> UI : Return Rendered Partial View\nor JSON Dataset
deactivate Controller

UI --> User : Display Results Overlay
deactivate UI

@enduml
